    "comment": "Rationale: Fig 2 a,b Synaptic Plasticity Is Altered by the Loss of GIT Expression\nLiteral \"Figure 2 shows that at all frequencies tested there was a significant reduction in the PPR in both the Git1-/- or Git1-/-Git2-/- calyces, but not the Git2-/-\nFig 2c,d GIT1 regulates frequency dependent synaptic plasticity.\nLiteral \"We found an increase in the rate of onset of depression and lower steady state levels with the loss of GIT1 alone, and this amount of depression was not increased with loss of both GIT1 and GIT2 together\n\n10/11/2017 Pim\n- Git1 was deleted in the presynapse specifically, but GIT2 was a global KO.. Experimental description: All the experiments were done in mice\nLiteral \"Afferent fiber stimulation and presynaptic recordings were performed as previously described on P16-21 mice\"",
